text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think itâ€™s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people donâ€™t necessarily know itâ€™s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so itâ€™s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that youâ€™re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of peopleâ€™s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldnâ€™t have seen, and couldnâ€™t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, â€œwould work for anyoneâ€. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean theyâ€™re mercenaries. theyâ€™ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

text:
wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

bannon worked on trump's campaign and became a white house aide when trump took office in january 2017. bannon left in august 2017.

wylie, who has provided reports about how the firm used data facebook collected, on wednesday described discussions at the company about suppressing the vote, exploiting racial tensions, and testing campaign slogans in 2014 for use in the 2016 election. - one of the things that did provoke me to leave was the beginnings of discussions of voter disengagement, i have seen documents reference and i recall conversations that it was intended to focus on african-american voters, wylie said. - the company learned that there were segments of the population that responded to messages like 'drain the swamp' or images of border walls or indeed paranoia about the 'deep state' that weren't necessarily reflected in mainstream polling or mainstream political discourse that steve bannon was interested in to help build his movement, wylie said.

another witness who testified to the judiciary committee, tufts university associate professor eitan hersh, said he was "skeptical" of the effectiveness that such political messaging and targeting. - no person is persuadable all the time, he said.

mark hosenball
reuters

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - iâ€™ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now iâ€™m about to go back, knowing what i know, and weâ€™re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trumpâ€™s election, trumpeted the return of their â€œpopulist heroâ€ on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publicationâ€™s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if thereâ€™s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: iâ€™m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents â€“ on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

text:
as post regarding r kelly flood my tl, im seeing alot of people ask why did they wait so long to come forward. speaking as a survivor of molestation and sexual abuse during the ages 14 -19, i can say from horrible experience that the mental brainwashing that happens is so subtle and unimaginable that in most circumstances you cant and won't understand that your being abused. i wasn't held down and forceably raped, instead my offenders (there were 2 from my church) became my friends gained my trust and that of my family's. they got me to open up about my relationship with my then boyfriend and pretended to comfort me and give advice to help. little did i know they were just seeing if i was a good candidate for silence. the helplessness, embarrassment, shame and eradication of self esteem and self love almost happens simultaneously. i kept my first abuse secret for 4 years and my second abuse secret for 21 years. my offenders had people on their side who knew what they were doing, yet never spoke up. one had and still has a wife that feels no remorse for her husband's actions. she guilted me into silence even more after he told her what he did to me. my 2nd offender told me that he picked me to abuse because he knew i was loyal and wouldn't tell anyone, because that could effect his ministry. the cognitive retraining that has to happen to young victims to think in a normal healthy space again is tremendous and takes years. pedophiles and habitual abusers in general choose their prey carefully for optimal probability of silence, compliance and ease of abuse. so for those curious as to why survivors wait so long to come forward, i hope my perspective and first hand account of my own abuse provides a better understanding for you.
.
.
#metoo #churchtoo #iwontbesilent #wewontbesilent #mytruth #theonlytruth #ihopemyoffendersseethis #whataboutthechildren #depression #guilt #mentalheath #selflove #selfcare #victim #survivor #victimturnedsurvivor #allthingsang

this #femalefounderfriday we're highlighting jessica o. matthews, a nigerian-american inventor, ceo and venture capitalist. she is the co-founder of uncharted power, which made soccket, a soccer ball that can be used as a power generator. matthews attended harvard college and graduated from harvard business school. in 2011, fortune magazine named her fortuneâ€™s "10 most powerful women entrepreneurs" and in 2015, named her as fortuneâ€™s "most promising women entrepreneurs." in 2012, the harvard foundation for intercultural and race relations named her "scientist of the year." matthews is a dual citizen of the u.s. and nigeria. the president of nigeria named matthews an ambassador for entrepreneurship for the country.

text:
chiron shiz
.
the end of 2018 has not gone out with a whimper, amirite? presided over by a waning scorpio moon, andÂ the sharp pain of a separating mars-chiron conjunction, i canâ€™t remember the last time i have ugly-cried more than these past few weeks. the wounded healer is already freighted with a great deal of collective trauma, his fetlocks stiff with mud as he traverses endless, spongy moors. with saturn reverb so relentless in the atmos as well, the past few days have felt like one of those dreams where your limbs feel draggingly heavy, and itâ€™s impossible to wrangle your tongue into a scream.
.
mars, however, is the shrapnel turning in an ancient hurt; perhaps growth is finally pushing those sharps to the surface. i think of wounds so deeply infected, either amputation or cauterization is needed. we have been forced to let go of something precious in this dark of the moonâ€”coins and jacks and ticket stubs falling from the hanged manâ€™s pockets. the pain of this loss may have blindsided us, even if we let go of something ultimately soul-eroding. even the most posionous stories we tell ourselves can become cornerstones for entire cosmologies; we pretend they keep us alive. but the devil is the lord of lies.
.
in terms of zeitgeist, it feels appropriate that heel-turns by kevin spacey and louis c.k., both accused of sexual assault during #metoo, took off their masks at the end of this year. mars-chiron has felt like a spasm of toxic masculinity (and the road of healing is long, as chiron will have 10 years to sort through the sign of the masculine principle). spacey posted a youtube video rebuffing countless accusations, in character, as duplicitous murderer, frank underwoodâ€”a sort of feeble, meta, double breaking of the fourth wall (which was not half as clever as he thought it was).
.
c.kâ€™s latest stand-up, a puerile punching down of school shooting victims, and trans millennials, hardly merits mention. i could go on about c.kâ€™s sun-pluto conjunction: his life was destined to be marked by spectacular gains and losses, an opportunity to evolve and settle into the power, and indeed compassion, of a survivor and pilgrim of the underworld. but no.
.
(continuedâ¬‡)

i donâ€™t particularly like showing my vulnerable side on social media and therefore have not talked much about my depression, anxiety or ptsd. but, this year, i am going to try to be more open because with openness comes acceptance, understanding and true healing.

text:
when i left an abusive relationship, i remember saying: i just want to be respected. i didnâ€™t fully realize that respect was not reciprocated until i left him. he had no regard for my feelings, rights, wishes, opinions, thoughts, etc. to him all that mattered was his own, so he refused to see that i too was a person in the relationship with equal needs and value.
.
someone who doesnâ€™t respect you will not know how to love and care about you. they are not capable of an equal partnership. stay clear of those who disrespect you.
.
.
.

text:
@dangerousfemales is a collective of women fed up with the incidents of menâ€™s violence against women in this country.  the profits from these amazing shirts go directly to organisations assisting survivors of domestic and sexual violence.  they call themselves dangerous females because they want to take back ownership of the word danger.  too often, the media tells women it is too dangerous to walk alone at night, to go on a date, to wear skirts.  however, statistics show us it is actually the most dangerous for women to be in their own home in this country.

2018 was the year women fought back following the rise of #metoo in late 2017.  i am always astounded by all the dangerous females in my life - their courage, willingness to fight but more importantly, their increasing support for #wetoo as a sisterhood.  i canâ€™t wait to see what the queendom brings in 2019 #letsgogirls #dangerousfemales #instagay #gaylawyer

text:
this place used to be my home. the company made it living hell. 
i look back and think of who i willingly surrounded myself and cringe. i cant comprehend how i allowed myself to accept anything less than love. kindness and respect. 
my biggest lesson in life was one of self worth. 
this isnt a perception of who that person was, but a reality, a reflection of who i was to allow it. he took advantage of me at my worst and i got fished in with what seemed like love, but really was a lie he uses over and over to find someone to push around, to do his bidding. 
he found someone new to manipulate and abuse, and i sincerely hope and pray that she sees the lies for what they are. how his actions never line up with his lies of words. how he plays the victim while creating more. 
path of self destruction, except he takes you with him. 
fuck ride or die. relationships mean nothing without respect for the other person. 
fuck you

text:
this poem was written in july 2017 when i wrestled with the thought of silencing young women who were victims of molestation , rape , grooming etc. i wrote this to show ,especially where i am from, older women (often victims themselves) encouraged younger victims to bury their experiences deep in them . until it gnawed on their insides and they were forced to spit it out . they painted it as a strength saying that there was strength in women who could keep the secrets of these tragic events and live life unfazed . evidently, it is all a lie cooked up and handed to women for generations, there is no strength in silencing yourself . 
in light of recent events such as #metoo #metoomovement  and #survivingrkelly  i want to take this chance to let young survivors know that there is only strength in speaking out on these atrocities. may god see you through it all . 
#writersofinstagram #poetry #poem #poetrycommunity #poetsofinstagram #smashthepatriarchy #endmisogyny ~~~p.s. again the last line was edited because it was too blurry in my journal as it was written in pencil and iâ€™m pretty sure i cried on the page ... sorry if it causes any inconsistencies. ~~~ #africanwriters #africanwoman #nigerianwomendiary

description taken from the women march on: toronto - 2019 march facebook event page:
because we will not go back.
on january 19th, women march on: toronto invites you to join together in marching, resisting and making it clear to policymakers that we will not accept rollbacks and attacks on our communities. 
this march, and this movement, began in solidarity with our sisters in the united states as they demonstrated their resistance to their countryâ€™s new leadership. we march to bring awareness to the changes needed to build a safer, more inclusive toronto. we are doing it again this year.
our lineup of speakers will address the many egregious cutbacks to government funding and civil rights recently made by our provincial government. please note: speakers and performers are not listed in order of appearance.
land acknowledgement by dawn maracle
tanya tagaq
farrah khan with a member of youth gravity 
sandy hudson
rayne fisher-quann
melissa graham
yasmeen persad
megan whitfield
indigenous drummers
grrrl justice
raging asian women drumming circle
* confirmation of the march route is being finalized and will be available soon, along with an updated accessibility plan. accessibility vans and asl interpretation will be provided at the march.

all allies are welcome âœ¨

text:
a quiet man is not always one who is free of trauma.
(this post was hard to put together, and that showed us how necessary it was to talk about this.)
1 in 6 men will of have experienced some sort of sexual violence in their lifetime.
how can we help them heal?
we didn't want to speak for men, so we asked the question on social media today.
what do men need from us, as a specie, to help them heal past sexual trauma?
here are some of the answers we have collected from the men:
.
"we need non-judgement"
.
"for a man sexual trauma blows their manhood.
it creates a split internally.
sexuality becomes confusing.
he has needs and urges, but his shadow (trauma) follows him everywhere.
this gets complicated..."
.
"we need to feel like we won't be punished for what we're about to share."
.
"we prefer to tell our story to people who are already talking about the subject, in a space that is safe"
.
"we need tools to help us heal in a private a manner.
it is an individual matter.
people deal with trauma differently."
.
"we need to see more men talk about their trauma.
whether it's on tv, online or in real life."
.
"i only talk about it with women."
.
"men might not speak about it with women"
.
"we need to respect the growth of everyone and realize that some people are simply not ready to heal."
.
"men will speak to someone who truly wants to understand them.
who makes them feel like they matter and respected.
we only speak when we feel it's safe to speak."
.
-sayitvalencia
#metoo
#energyhealing 
#activelistening

text:
welcome to the trauma club
the price of admission is pretty high
it costs a time
or two 
or hundreds
where someone had to put themselves first
even though it broke you
or worse
where you had to save yourself
even though you knew it would break
someone else
yep admission costs a pretty penny
but once you're in
you're in for life
and membership comes with some
great perks
for instance
as a member
you'll feel like sometimes it's okay
to screw people over
won't have to deal with that pesky 
guilt shit
as much
anymore
yeah, it's okay because
they weren't smart enough
they weren't careful enough
they were too innocent
should have been looking out
should have seen it coming
like you would have
you pay the price of admission every day
never feeling safe
never trusting
and if more shit happens to you
you feel shame rather than anger
because you weren't smart enough
you weren't careful enough
and so it was your fault
listen
take it from someone who's been there 
and
gotten past some of the worst of it
not alone
but only with the help of many angels
who saw my innocence
when i couldn't see it
if you're in the trauma club 
like i am
hear this
forcing other people into the club too
so you can have some company who understands you for once
will make you feel more alone in the end
not less
let the angels guide you out
instead
be an angel yourself
even
your innocence 
is unbreakable
it's still there
everyone belongs in the light
come back to it
when you're ready
amen
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.

text: todayâ€™s feminist friday is dedicated to me too founder tarana burke. a long time feminist and african-american civil rights activist, tarana burke is best known as the founder of the me too movement in 2006. her activist career began in selma, alabama in the early 90s, where she started the nonprofit just be for the support of young black women. there, she began to use the phrase â€œme tooâ€ as a way to empathize and show solidarity with other survivors of sexual assault. the me too movement has since blossomed into a worldwide campaign to raise awareness about sexual harassment, abuse, and assault in society. in 2017, burke and other influential female activists were named "the silence breakers" by time magazine. she currently serves at the girls for gender equity in brooklyn as its senior director. â€œthereâ€™s a power in empathy.â€ #feministfriday #taranaburke #metoo

text:
hello there, my name is lauren and i am the one behind all of this. i know everyone and their brother has their own streetwear brand out there. the hustle, the grind, what ever, we're all doing it. what makes this different though is that for me, i am doing this all myself and i'm deeply rooted to why i am doing this. when i was a kid in school i felt very isolated from people. my environment changed all the time. it lead me to dealing with a lot of loneliness and depression. i was bullied a lot as a kid, the classic kind where they shove you into lockers, chase you down the street, and fight you. i was even called a devil worshiper a lot because of my dark clothes. it sticks with ya, i know. then in college i had an experience that really had me crying #metoo. i've had support systems fail, i've been scared to ask for help, and i've felt helpless. rather than telling others "it gets better" i'd like to just show you, and be the avenue in which i believe that through all the dark times the good always comes back around. that's where damaged kids comes from. turning pain into a positive thing by owning it as apart of the story. because as a kid i felt better seeing other kids wear band tshirts i identified with, i'm building a brand just like that but instead it will feel like 'i identify with how you feel' and it'll just be ok. whether you identify with that or not, is fine with me. this is for anyone who needs it. â €

text:
first vulnerability post of the new year. 
read below â¤µï¸â¤µï¸â¤µï¸ most people in my life know that since high school i have worked on becoming healthier physically through new ways of eating, new fitness routines, physio routines for my back, etc. 2018 was the year that i started working on being mentally healthier too. i am amazed with how far i've come and the changes i've been able to make because i now have these two pieces of the puzzle working together.

the confidence and courage to share this is something i look to work on in 2019! to be less focused on being perfect on social media (really no one cares about this) and instead share how things are going for real. 
most people in my life don't know that i am a health and wellness coach. honestly, i know why people don't....because i've been too apprehensive to fully share my passion with people outside of my immediate supportive circle. well, i hope i have a supportive audience here, but regardless, i am sharing! 
it is my goal to create a space where i can work alongside other women like me that are looking for healthier and happier lives...or looking to just have something new and get out of old habits. 
my hope for 2019 is to meet women of all careers, body sizes, ages, fitness levels, and experiences and help them #riseup. 
it is my mission to bring that "spring in my step back" by working on my own mental and physical health. with coaching i can extend that to others!! #amazeballs

text:
i'm just tryna figure out who is gonna cop all blame that judging about with certain situations in this thing called life. i love my siblings, but am i suppose to turn a blind on the age difference that my father had over some of their moms? because he married them, not just skeeted and left. 
even #metoo founder tarana burke says that her movement is "unrecognizable" now. 
i do not believe that a child looks to be molested or taken advantage of. however, i do believe that there may be a  child out here that are already doing grown shit liking cooking and cleaning for themselves and others, letting mommy or daddy get a few bills in their name, using their csc on bills instead of them, watching family members instead of being a child. and if you were that grown child, do not let these documentaries, comments or society make you feel like a victim. you did what tf you wanted to do. own your shit! most of the parasuco honies i knew from hs wasn't always switching clothes, they had grown in age friends, but also realized that some of them were more mentally immature than their hs age ğŸ˜ğŸ˜’ğŸ˜ğŸ˜’ so to the come sit on my lap muthafuckas, y'all know y'all wrong but some of y'all are free because society is trying to lump everything under 1 category to keep us under overpopulated surveillance. 
to the ones that say they had no business dating older people... be glad you didn't die and you're here to say that, but remember what you're saying you did. like hiding it from your family... your family that was probably once country and african as fuck!! ((insert torie stepping in the name of love)) âœŒâœŒâœŒâœŒâœŒğŸƒğŸƒğŸƒâ˜•â˜•â˜•â˜•ğŸ™ğŸ™ğŸ™ #surviving #life #balanceyoungniggabalance #youaintgottahaveyourjudgementupforeverythingifyounotgonnajudgeitall

text:
project reflecting on a woman's wish to be seen and her simultaneous impulse to hide herself, after centuries of misogynistic programming.

for centuries, women have been reduced solely to their appearance, their physical beauty deemed their only worth. western philosophers who have shaped our collective thinking -Â aristotle[i], socrates[ii], jean-jacques rousseau[iii], darwin[iv], schopenhauer[v], nietzsche[vi] -Â compared women to animals, incapable of rational thought, devoid of intelligence. and although present generations are desperately trying to escape these narrow confinements, the ingrained programming leaves many women struggling with their self-worth.

the objectification of the female body is an effective form of dehumanization. women's sexuality is exploited and suppressed at the same time. admired and reviled, chased and judged, praised and ridiculed.Â this opppresive societal schizophrenia is mirrored in every woman's soul.

this series reflects on the desire to be seen, coupled with the shame and instinctive need to hide.

text:
these posts, this performance, was a celebration of the transformative powers that we hold. of the ways in which we face our worst fears everyday and come out on the winning side. that's the way that we transform horror into beauty. the way that we endure these atrocities, yet still walk the streets, our heads held high proud of the fact that we have survived one more day. of how we choose to love and how we choose to grow and how we choose kindness even in the face of death. that's how we survive oh, that's how we endure, that is why we are brave. when the sound of the world as we walk on by is that of hatred and violence, degredation and inhumanity, we still live our truth everyday and that is to be celebrated. you are to be celebrated. this is to remind you of what you've been through, though you can never forget. this is to remind you how far you come and have progressed and grown. that you live and succeed even when you feel behind. this is to remind you that for us to survive in this world is for us to rebel. and you are not alone. i am here for you, we are here for you and no matter what this world has to throw at you, no matter how painful or destructive, i will not walk on by. there is a place for you, with me, and it is safe. a community.
.
â¤ï¸ @heavenly_powers thank you for sharing this moment with me, thank you for trusting me, for loving me, for being willing to display this moment of awful vulnerability with me. thank you for being my friend. thank you for sacrificing yourself to make this real, thank you for existing and inspiring me. thank you for reminding me that even after trauma, i deserve to be loved. thank you for all the time and effort and patience you put into helping me make this performance what it was.
.

text:
louis c.k. exposes his racism like a common penis

audio surfaced this weekend of rightly disgraced comedian louis c.k. performing a set at a levittown, new york, club on december 16. the timing was unfortunate because c.k.'s career just missed inclusion on all the 2018 celebrity deaths lists.
after finally admitting, against his will, to repeatedly masturbating in front of women comics against their will, c.k. promised to "now step back and take a long time to listen." it was like the intro to a sex offender version of "the real world." it seems he's spent that year listening to right-wing media and stewing in his own bile. his december act was repulsive and cruel. it's not the product of self-reflection but incensed rage that he has been held mildly accountable for his actions.
where do you start with such garbage? how about where he implicitly blames women -- you know, the people he victimized -- for the pc culture that he doubtless believes led to his downfall. in the minds of men like c.k., it is always nagging women, or emasculated men, telling them what they can or can't say.
"i was kind of excited to be in my 50s and see people in their 20s and be like, 'you're crazy! these kids are nuts,' but they're not! they're fuckin' like 'nyeaah.' they're just boring. fuckin' tellin' ,' you shouldn't say that.' what are you? an old lady? what the fuck are you doing? 'nyeeah, that's not appropriate.' fuck you. you're a child.' "
i dunno. i think if you're a grown man who's "confused" about the appropriateness of masturbating in front of women in a professional setting, you probably should consider listening to children. they are clearly smarter than you. 
#louisck #notfunny #parklandstudents #asshole #metoo #cancelled #nobodywantedtoseeyourpeniscreep

text:
âœ¨each time i stumble i try to remember this truth...
.
.
the comeback is always bigger the setback.
.
.
donâ€™t believe me?
.
.
here is a quick share of a true story from my journey:
.
.
once upon a time past i started my business in la way before the #metoo movement.
.
.
as part of my strategy to gain influence and referrals, i joined the chamber of commerce. as the newest member of my chapter, i attended a networking event.
.
.
a man approached me right away, hand outstretched, business card thrust into my gaze. he was a lawyer and much older than me. welcoming me with the endearing term â€œfresh meatâ€ he offered to introduce me to his inner circle of â€œbros.â€ he did not even know what i did for work mind you.
.
.
at last he paused long enough for me to say i owned a pilates studio and specialized in using pilates to rehabilitate injuries.
.
.
his reply left me speechless: â€œmy, you must be super flexible...what is your favorite sexual position?â€
.
.
like a doe in oncoming headlights i froze. no words surfaced to my awareness. i had no comeback.
.
.
he seemed oblivious to my discomfort. maybe he said this sort of thing often. tapping his foot impatiently, apparently he was waiting for me to actually answer his query.
.
.
all i could do was pivot away from him, saying i had to go meet my boyfriend.
.
.
fast forward half a decade. that same man attended a party one of my celebrity clients hosted. by this time my business flourished, my client base was filled by word-of-mouth referrals and i had learned how to deal with men in a different way.
.
.
not knowing my past encounter, my client introduced me to the attorney. apparently he hoped my client would join him in a new venture.
.
.
pulling my client aside i shared the details of my past meeting with the man. horrified she offered to throw him out of the event. stopping her i offered another alternative.
.
.
approaching the man along with my client i reminded him how we already knew one another. i told him i had an answer to his question: me on top.
.
.
then my client told him she would not be joining his venture and for him to find the exit.
.
.
like i said, the comeback is always bigger than the setback.âœ¨

text:
ğŸ”Š#weshallbeheardğŸ”Š
we are beyond excited to once again host and organize the 3rd annual women's march on philadelphia on january 19th, 2019. our theme this year is "we shall be heard"!
ğŸ”Šwe shall be heard in our neighborhoods as we organize for action against gun violence, racism, antisemitism and islamophobia.
ğŸ”Šwe shall be heard in the workplace where we expect equal pay for equal work and say #timesup to sexual harassment and assault.
ğŸ”Šwe shall be heard by the politicians who represent us on women's reproductive rights including safe and legal abortion, low cost healthcare for all, free college tuition, lgbtq rights and anti-discrimination policies, a pathway to citizenship and immigration reform, protection for the right and the ability for all citizens to vote and climate change policy.
ğŸ”Šwe hope that you will join us at 10am at eakins oval as we march down the ben franklin parkway to the philadelphia art museum where we will rally with a list of amazing speakers that represent all that we are fighting for.
ğŸ”Šwith only a few weeks to go, we cannot do this without your help! our organization is an all volunteer board that is dedicated to these causes and donates our time to the planning and execution of this amazing event. donations are needed to pay for all of the various vendors for the event including sound, audio/visual, tents, ada seating, portable restrooms, lighting, etc...to do this right we need $50,000. if everyone whoâ€™s attended the march donates $5 we will meet our goal! thank you for your support!ğŸ™ğŸ¾
.
ğŸ”Što donate: https://donorbox.org/women-s-march-on-philadelphia
.
ğŸ”Što read more click here: http://www.womensmarchphl.com
.
.

text:
as posted earlier, i was supposed to speak at the #indiadialogues on the #metoo movement on this sunday. but i just got this program poster today. after having a long look at it, i have decided to pull out of the event.
my reason for canceling stems from the fact that not a single woman has been deemed worthy of the 7 keynotes. also, as the poster makes it clear - the organisers didn't find the panel on #metoo deserving of a keynote. i, then, expressed my concerns to the organisers who pointed out the presence of a few women speakers. but my contention about lack of women keynote speakers remains. having a few women as tokens while the men are still put at the centre stage is rather disheartening especially in the aftermath of #metoo. as a feminist, i feel it is my duty to flag the brazenness of male privilege. 
therefore, i have conveyed to the organisers that women are done being subjected to the sidelines. i cannot be a part of this.

text:
why this picture is important enough to me to post:
my depression takes over my life. i can go weeks without showering, weeks without changing clothes, and weeks without eating more than a handful of times. itâ€™s gross i know, but it is 100% my reality. i find joy in so little, which i know seems weird as i am by nature an optimist. 
oddly enough i had a dream last night about the @thebucketlistfamily family. (random i know but it has a point.) my family and i went on vacation with them and in this dream we saw first hand that they live the way they do in all their posts. they were generous, kind, open, free, complete lovers of life. the craziest thing was they are completely ordinary people, but ordinary people with the right vision, which makes them extraordinary.
now, that bit of information may seem super random but when i woke this morning something in my brain had switched while sleeping. *living authentically is the foundation to joy & freedom.*
i woke up and i made my bed, i walked in my bathroom and washed my face and brushed my teeth. i looked in the mirror and smiled dammit! like, hello? what is happening haha. i then got dressed, fully dressed in new clean clothes. like, yeah, i have real pants on and a bra. i put earrings on!
then i extra surprised myself by making myself breakfast and a cup of tea. all with my kids running around and me not at the end of my rope with anxiety. i just listened in on the chaos and... enjoyed it. not handled it, i enjoyed it.
this picture signifies a complete turning point for me. i thought by 28 iâ€™d be mentally well, kicking ass and taking names, and have created an amazing career... but i havenâ€™t. this morning i woke up with, so what?! i can still do that! iâ€™ll just be older now.
my depression hit me like a wrecking ball when i was 6, when my innocence was wrecked and taken by a really sick guy. thatâ€™s a story for another time, but iâ€™m fully committed in this moment to fully and completely no longer be a victim to a really shitty hand of cards that was dealt to me a long time ago.
this is part of me living more authentically, claiming my ugly. 2019 = authenticity. âœŠğŸ¼

sixty percent of black girls have experienced sexual abuse at the hands of  men before reaching the age of 18, according to an ongoing study conducted by black womenâ€™s blueprint.

additionally:

1 in 4 black girls will be sexually abused before the age of 18. (stone, r.d., no secrets, no lies: how black families can heal from sexual abuse, 2004)

thirty percent of black women with documented histories of childhood sexual abuse were sexually assaulted in adulthood. (siegel & williams, risk factors for sexual victimization of women, violence against women 9, 2003)

for every black woman who reports a rape, at least 15 do not report (bureau of justice statistics, 2009)

beyond these facts are our personal narratives on the issues of pedophilia and sexual violence (which also go hand-in-hand) in the black community. if you gather 10 black women in a room, it is likely that at least nine have been victims of pedophilia, street harassment, and/or sexual assault; or they have a friend, cousin, sister, aunt, mother, or grandmother who has been victimized.

text: people with privilege do not want to discuss their privilege â€” whether itâ€™s privilege derived from whiteness, straightness, cisness. but we must acknowledge our privilege if we are to dismantle systems and hierarchies.  having a body that society deems as beautiful and struggling to accept your size is a different experience than living in a body that society deems as wrong and hating your body. one experience comes with external validation regarding how you view your body. the other does not. (itâ€™s not my place nor do i believe in ranking suffering so my comments are not directed that way). however we need to start getting loud and speaking about the subtle but major differences and owning our privilege if we do live in a body that diet culture has stamped as acceptable. body positivity was intended to be political. letâ€™s get back to that so that we are working towards all bodies being valued in society. we have to be honest about our privilege. we have to be honest about how we benefit from our â€œbeautyâ€. i have benefitted, have you?

text:
learned about a pioneer of not only medicine but civil rights while atÂ stanford university school of medicineÂ the other day and thought this would be extremely relevant especially with the climate we are living in.

dr. frances k. conleyÂ in 1975 she became the first female faculty member at stanford in any surgical department, in 1977, she became the fifth woman to become a board certified neurosurgeon in the united states, in 1982 the first woman to be granted a tenured professorship in neurosurgery at a u.s. medical school and in 1986, the first to have a full professorship.

in june 1991, she publicly resigned from @stanford universityÂ in protest over the work environment that included sexist attitudes and outright sexual harassment.Â when conley resigned from stanford university, her book walking out on the boys was released and provided a very in depth and first hand look at the sexism that really went on at the university. 
#metoo #medicine #pioneer #trailblazer #neurosurgery

text: growing up obsessed with pop culture, i was aware of who the alpha males were in the performing arts. guys who swigged their drinks and gave their opinions to swooning fans. your robert culps and conrads... your chad everetts. the james coburns, lee marvins. of course the burts and clints. sinatras and dinos. jerry lewis. the goulets. guys. swinging dicks. it wasnâ€™t until later in the thousand different drama departments of the thousand different colleges i drifted through that i locked into alpha playwrights. eric bogosian who also acted, mostly in solo performances but occasionally in ensemble plays where he limited himself to one character in the cast. and, of course, david mamet, the moses of playwrights. a man who didnâ€™t just write, he laid. down. the law. heâ€™s written as many essay collections, think pieces, op eds and given as many interviews, as a 24 hr cycle of pundits, all the while calmly puffing on his cigar and brooking no discourse. he has gone from giving to assholes poetic self justification in the form of blistering plays to defending libertarians and conservatives. sinatra once said something along the lines of â€œif youâ€™re young youâ€™re a democrat unless you have no heart. when youâ€™re old, youâ€™re a republican unless you have no brain.â€ as if a change of politics was a simple as following the yellow brick road. mamet has taken that change to be a bright north star of belligerence. bogosian, on the other hand, has gone from rockstar solo performance/creator to respected character actor. i yearn for another collection of male characters to be written and performed by him- maybe this time to see the #metoo movement through the defensive eyes of the blubbering men who thought they were â€œsensitive.â€ or maybe he sees too much of that already played out in reality. eric bogosianâ€™s playwriting showed a blinding light on dark, secret corners. we have that happening every day now, thanks to #metoo and #timesup. maybe the last thing they need is the male opinion. maybe itâ€™s time to stop looking for alpha males to give their take. #ericbogosian #davidmamet #alphamale #franksinatra

text:
january is national stalking awareness month!
_
sasc's website goes into more detail about the signs of stalking, the behaviors exhibited by those who stalk, and what you can do if you are being stalked.  the state of georgia has the ability to grant a temporary protection order (tpo) for those who are victims of stalking, and sasc can accompany those who are in need to obtain a tpo. 
_
for more information please contact us or visit our website: http://www.sexualassaultsupportcenter.com/stalking.html
_

in the 90s he married a teenager and then years later allegedly he was on video having sex, giving money and golden showers to a minor... the defense argued the man in the video was not kelly, and the girl in video was not a minor... he was acquitted. â€œeight of the seated jurors were white and four were black, and that remained the jury's racial makeup after a white female juror was replaced tuesday morning by one of four alternates, a white male.â€ - thr 5/2008 "the 27-minute homemade video shows a man having sex with a young female, who is naked for most of the recording except for a necklace with a cross dangling from it.

at the start of the videotape, the man hands the female money and she mouths the words, "thank you." she is often blank-faced, impassive. the man speaks to the female in a hushed, monotone voice, and she calls him "daddy." songs from the spice girls and backstreet boys blare from a radio. the female dances -- the man out of view. back in view, he has sex with her. the man walks up to the camera to adjust it a few times, but his face is often obscured.

prosecutors say the man in the video is kelly, and that the female is a girl who was as young as 13 when the tape was made between jan. 1, 1998, and nov. 1, 2000.

the singer, who has pleaded not guilty, faces up to 15 years if convicted.

during opening statements in the long-delayed trial, cook county prosecutor shauna boliker warned jurors they would have to watch a videotape depicting an "underage child performing sex acts that you have never seen before." "a child doesn't choose to be violated and placed on a videotape, a videotape that will live on forever -- long after this child becomes an adult," boliker said.

defense attorneys, however, told jurors in their opening statements that kelly is not the man on the tape and called the video's origins into question. the defense also told jurors that the girl who authorities allege is depicted on the tape is not her at all.  #metoo #whosnext #rkelly

during opening statements in the long-delayed trial, cook county prosecutor shauna boliker warned jurors they would have to watch a videotape depicting an "underage child performing sex acts that you have never seen before." "a child does not choose to be violated and placed on a videotape, a videotape that will live on forever -- long after this child becomes an adult," boliker said.

defense attorneys, however, told jurors in their opening statements that kelly is not the man on the tape and called the video's origins into question. the defense also told jurors that the girl who authorities allege is depicted on the tape is not her at all.

text:
disclaimer: trigger warning
.
i debated with myself for a while regarding when and how much of my story i planned on sharing...and given the fact that i have decided to stand in my personal power and speak my truth i have decided that i am going to share it all, to be an open book and speak out in hope of maybe helping others find their voice and speak out (even if it is just to a few trusted friends or family members) so that they are able to heal.
.
now with that out of the way, here is the public police announcement of my story: .
on december 5, 2018, at approximately 1:45 pm, deputies were dispatched to the walmart located at 11550 meridian market view, in unincorporated el paso county for a report of a stranger kidnapping and sexual assault.
.
the victim exited the store and loaded groceries into her vehicle.Â  as she returned the cart, the suspect walked towards her unlocked vehicle and entered the rear passenger door.Â  when the victim returned to her vehicle, the suspect held her at gunpoint with a handgun, and told her to drive. .
the suspect directed her from the parking lot to a remote location, where he raped her.Â  he forced the victim to drive back towards the walmart where he made her park behind the store.  the suspect then walked back to his vehicle. .
it is possible he attempted to contact another female and tried to get into her vehicle, just prior to this event.
.
through community tips and tenacious investigative work, the suspect was located in aurora, colorado.Â  on december 7, 2018, at approximately 9:00 pm, the el paso county sheriff's office along with the aurora police department swat responded to the 1200 block of s. zeno circle, and the suspect subsequently took his life.
.
we would like to extend our gratitude to our community for calling in with tips and the aurora police department for their assistance in this case. *end*
.
in 30 short seconds my life changed forever...30 seconds and someone decided to try and snuff out my light with their ugliness.  but i'm here, i'm alive...i am not a victim, i'm a fucking survivor!
.
you are a survivor
name: Raye Sweezea

i debated with myself for a while regarding when and how much of my story i planned on sharing...and given the fact that i have decided to stand in my personal power and speak my truth i have decided that i am going to share it all, to be an open book and speak out in hope of maybe helping others find their voice and speak out (even if it is just to a few trusted friends or family members) so that they are able to heal.
.
now with that out of the way, here is the public police announcement of my story: .
on december 5, 2018, at approximately 1:45 pm, deputies were dispatched to the walmart located at 11550 meridian market view, in unincorporated el paso county for a report of a stranger kidnapping and sexual assault.
.
the victim exited the store and loaded groceries into her vehicle.Â  as she returned the cart, the suspect walked towards her unlocked vehicle and entered the rear passenger door.Â  when the victim returned to her vehicle, the suspect held her at gunpoint with a handgun, and told her to drive. .
the suspect directed her from the parking lot to a remote location, where he raped her.Â  he forced the victim to drive back towards the walmart where he made her park behind the store.  the suspect then walked back to his vehicle. .
it is possible he attempted to contact another female and tried to get into her vehicle, just prior to this event.
.
through community tips and tenacious investigative work, the suspect was located in aurora, colorado.Â  on december 7, 2018, at approximately 9:00 pm, the el paso county sheriff's office along with the aurora police department swat responded to the 1200 block of s. zeno circle, and the suspect subsequently took his life.
.
we would like to extend our gratitude to our community for calling in with tips and the aurora police department for their assistance in this case. *end*
.
in 30 short seconds my life changed forever...30 seconds and someone decided to try and snuff out my light with their ugliness.  but i am here, i am alive...i am not a victim, i am a fucking survivor!
.
you are a survivor

"youâ€™ve probably heard a story like this beforeâ€¦

once, i went to a party. i was drunk, in a pretty black dress. there was a man there. he made me very uncomfortable. whenever i left a room, he followed me. always one step behind me, watching me. he would try to wrap himself around me in dark corners, and i would push him off me and walk away. i told my friends, but they were too intoxicated to realise how upset i was. i went to bed alone in the spare room that night. i was not alone for long.

the next morning, i woke up broken. i woke up wondering what i could have done to prevent it. i had been drunk. i had been alone. i had been dressed in a pretty black dress. it was my fault. i truly believed that. so i said nothing.

but it wasnâ€™t my fault. and the girls that have lost their lives at the hands of violent men? it wasnâ€™t their fault either.

this is a problem with men, not women. but i cant change men, or how they choose to behave. i can only change myself, and the person i allow myself to be. i decided after that day that i would become a woman that a man would severely regret choosing as his victim."

text:
what we do -

justice for lai dai han is a group that gives a voice to the victims of sexual violence and campaigns for south korea to recognise and apologise for widespread rape and sexual violence against vietnamese women in the vietnam war.

our work seeks to raise public awareness, to allow community leaders to connect with the victims of sexual violence to understand their suffering first hand and to create public art as a permanent reminder of the plight of the lai dai han.
.
.
.
.
.

in the 90s he married a teenager and then years later allegedly he was on video having sex, giving money and golden showers to a minor... the defense argued the man in the video was not kelly, and the girl in video was not a minor... he was acquitted. â€œeight of the seated jurors were white and four were black, and that remained the jury's racial makeup after a white female juror was replaced tuesday morning by one of four alternates, a white male.â€ - thr 5/2008 "the 27-minute homemade video shows a man having sex with a young female, who is naked for most of the recording except for a necklace with a cross dangling from it.

at the start of the videotape, the man hands the female money and she mouths the words, "thank you." she is often blank-faced, impassive. the man speaks to the female in a hushed, monotone voice, and she calls him "daddy." songs from the spice girls and backstreet boys blare from a radio. the female dances -- the man out of view. back in view, he has sex with her. the man walks up to the camera to adjust it a few times, but his face is often obscured.

prosecutors say the man in the video is kelly, and that the female is a girl who was as young as 13 when the tape was made between jan. 1, 1998, and nov. 1, 2000.

the singer, who has pleaded not guilty, faces up to 15 years if convicted.

during opening statements in the long-delayed trial, cook county prosecutor shauna boliker warned jurors they would have to watch a videotape depicting an "underage child performing sex acts that you have never seen before." "a child doesn't choose to be violated and placed on a videotape, a videotape that will live on forever -- long after this child becomes an adult," boliker said.

defense attorneys, however, told jurors in their opening statements that kelly is not the man on the tape and called the video's origins into question. the defense also told jurors that the girl who authorities allege is depicted on the tape is not her at all.  #metoo #whosnext #rkelly

text:
lifetime is presenting a three part documentary titled surviving r kelly this week.  for those who aren't familiar, r kelly is an american r&b artist who has has released music for 3 decades. he is the self proclaimed "pied piper of r&b". a term that is all too befitting seeing as how he likes to lure minors into his grips for his sexual pleasure. he was married to r&b singer aaliyah when she was just 15 and he was 27. he has also been tied to countless other minors according to the testimony provided by numerous women and men who were interviewed for this documentary. each person either told a story of personal sexual abuse they endured as a minor or sexual abuse they witnessed while working with him. he was even arrested for a video that surfaced years ago where he was allegedly seen urinating on a 13 yr old girl and engaging in sexual acts. now that you have context for who we are talking about, let's get into it....
every single person who watched this man go to the mall and the local high school to pick up minors, talked to minors on his behalf, transported minors, and overlooked him sexually abusing a minor is an accomplice! every person who referred to him being in a "relationship" with these minors is an accomplice! everyone who turned a blind eye to the suffering and abuse of these kids is an accomplice! you cannot cry enough tears or feign enough ignorance to excuse your willing participation in the abuse of these girls. there were countless opportunities for people to speak up and contact the authorities about what they witnessed, but his behavior was allowed to go unchecked for years. and  one would likely ask themselves why, and the answer is clear - too many value money over people and people don't really care about children as much as they say they do. as a society we talk about pimps, dealers, and other criminals, but what about the people who sell children everyday by turning a blind eye to sexual abuse at the hands of people they know? are they not as low as the pimp or domestic minor sex trafficker? at the end of the day, r kelly should have been stopped years ago and every adult who sat by and let this abuse go on is just as guilty as he is.

every single person who watched this man go to the mall and the local high school to pick up minors, talked to minors on his behalf, transported minors, and overlooked him sexually abusing a minor is an accomplice! every person who referred to him being in a "relationship" with these minors is an accomplice! everyone who turned a blind eye to the suffering and abuse of these kids is an accomplice! you cannot cry enough tears or feign enough ignorance to excuse your willing participation in the abuse of these girls. there were countless opportunities for people to speak up and contact the authorities about what they witnessed, but his behavior was allowed to go unchecked for years. and  one would likely ask themselves why, and the answer is clear - too many value money over people and people do not really care about children as much as they say they do. as a society we talk about pimps, dealers, and other criminals, but what about the people who sell children everyday by turning a blind eye to sexual abuse at the hands of people they know? are they not as low as the pimp or domestic minor sex trafficker? at the end of the day, r kelly should have been stopped years ago and every adult who sat by and let this abuse go on is just as guilty as he is.

text:
let me tell yâ€™all what we are not going to do in 2019, make little black girls the villains. 
r.kelly is a serial abuser. the fact he too was abused does not negate that he been stealing little girls since before he married a 15 year old aailiyah (may her spirit be resting in peace). i do not need to hear from him to know who to believe. 
and if your rebuttal about whether he needs to be brought to justice or not is â€œoh he been abused tooâ€, i say if you want to prevent r.kellys from coming to be then you need to make a world where it is not safe, or acceptable for r.kellys to do what they do. 
we must end rape culture, we must end poverty, we must end racism, we must end misogyny,  we must end white supremacy and so on and so forth. these are systems that support, reinforce, protect and glorify abusers. they must all go. 
black liberation is asking us to divest of abuser dynamics today! 
and in conclusion let me say this to you who need to know it:

you didnâ€™t deserve what happened to you, you didnâ€™t deserve not to be believed, you didnâ€™t deserve for your abuser to make it feel like it was your fault, you didnâ€™t deserve to suffer in silence, you didnâ€™t deserve for people to make it feel like your healing was a burden, you didnâ€™t deserve what happened to you and neither did any of these little girls.

text:
trigger warning: sexual abuse 
you never have to disclose a sexual assault or abuse, unless you want to. there's no timeframe on when you have to share that information either. however if someone shares that with you believe them, without questioning a motive. people have their own reasons for holding on or letting go something as personal as that. their reasons however are none of your business. even if nobody else believes, i believe you. there's nothing wrong with seeking professional help if you're struggling to move past it. i am a survivor and so are you. nobody has the right to take that from you. #canwegodeep #sextherapy #relationshiptherapy #counseling #therapy #sexualabuse #mentalhealth #sexualassault #sexeducation #support #selfcare #metoo #lifetime #mhgreatdebate

text:
the two cs running the last few kilometres on pakiri beach in new zealand. i was still so blissfully ignorant of what lay ahead of me on the journey. i think the reality did start to sink in on that run. i laughed and cried during this run. the tears came for the wild beauty and aloneness i experienced on this beach, as well as the sheer pain of running the last 8 kilometres into a headwind that felt like it was holding me in one spot. the laughter came in the last 2 kilometres when this wonderful little girl came bounding to me, giggling and smiling with joy, her cute pink dress and curly hair blowing in the wind. we share the same name just in different languages. little c's joy was contagious - a sweet reminder to enjoy the moment and to keep on running. 45 countries later i am still running and i still remember this beautiful moment as if it was yesterday. i guess there are certain memories that mark us forever, even change who we are as a human being.â €
*â €
i ran in nz on saturday 20 august 2016 - country 3 of the footsteps to inspire journey. â €
* â €
ğŸ“· thank you my dear jess and little c for sharing this moment and taking the great photos. â¤ï¸ you. â €

text:
respect goes both ways â†”ï¸ even if you do, too.

invariably, this post will be misunderstood by someone though that is not my intent. a friend commented on a fb post i made to warn me about the backlash someone else received for stating a viewpoint similar to the one i remarked upon. today, i stumbled across that controversial video. i don't find fault with his perspective nor his expression of it. he makes salient points. i say this, not solely because our points are so similar or because we have had common experiences but simply because he speaks truth to a taboo. 
this is not an "all lives matter" style attempt to weaken or undermine the lgbt movement, though objectively i can even understand the impulse to brand it as such. the difference is this, when a person refutes a romantic interest or a sexual advance, for any reason, simply respect their decision. if you get curved, keep it moving. this is not a "male or female" thing. not a "straight, gay, bi or lesbian" thing. this is an "i'm a person" thing. 
if you are offended by the video @christiankeyes shared (or even by this post) i welcome civil discourse with emotionally mature adults who have learned to agree to disagree. we can debate but you gotta argue by your damn self.

â€œdonâ€™t shoot the messenger.â€ some youtuber tells me. in horror, i realize my finger is on the trigger. remember my story from up north when i had a guy come on to me in an aggressive way? then flying out, another uninvited man approached me? i vowed the next creep was going to get both barrels. well, along he came, but i wrestled with blasting him for 3 wks. he felt unsafe. he triggered me every time we met. my uneasy mind would race but my heart & gut were calm. what?? in youtube land, clarity hit me, heâ€™s not a perv but a messenger. i put my verbal rifle down & looked at all the situations again with clear eyes. the common thoughts in all 3 scenarios was, â€œiâ€™m not safe. all men are takers.â€ the limited beliefs were exposed & so was the pile of messengers at my feet. in trauma, our brains develop filters that change what we see to â€œprotect usâ€. in this case, my brain was always proving men are toxic. this created fearful energy in me that attracted those kind of men. thankfully, forgiveness brings miracles. after healing the root issue, i met a guy. in parting, he hugged me & i felt pure love for him. no suspicion to his hug motives. why? because now, instead of seeing monsters, i see humans worthy of love. â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €

please, whatever you do, donâ€™t shoot the messenger. â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €

#womenwelove: "india's #metoo movement is driven by raw courage, given the retributive nature of calling out systemic violence and the patriarchy that enables it," says rituparna chatterjee (@rituparnachatterjee). the feminist and independent journalist who writes on gender politics and runs the @indiametoo twitter account, is one of bazaar's women we love this month.
more about chatterjee and her inspiring story in our jan-feb 2019 issue.

text: the men folk in my office were wankfest over how great noise cancelling headphones are. as a cis female i hate them. unless i'm driving in my car with my doors locked i don't even like having music at full volume. i tried them once and i had to keep pulling them about every 10 sec to assess my safety. #maleprivilege is not having to worry about if someone is following you...sure it would be nice to block out the cat calls but not at the risk of not getting home safely (or not at all). even in a professional office i'm still on guard about creepers keeping up behind me, invading my space, touching me, blocking/cornering. just thinking about not being able to hear what's happening around me makes me anxious af. am i the only one? is this one of those shared survival skills we all have in our collective consciousness like being wolverine with our keys? #fuckthepatriarchy #yesallwomen #metoo #feminism #equality #stopkillingus #donttouchme #personalspace #noisecancelling

text:
â€œdo you not know that your body is a temple of the holy spirit, who is in you, whom you have received from god? you are not your own; you were bought at a price. therefore honor god with your body.â€ 1 corinthians 6:19-20.
.
.
as a single woman living in this generation, it can be tempting to buy into the whole â€œi can do whatever i want with my bodyâ€ mentality, the belief that my body is my own, and what i do with it is my business. and for the sake of women empowerment, i can see why we default to thisâ€”this striving to be independent, in control, â€œself-confidentâ€ in who we are and what we do. itâ€™s our own way of â€œensuringâ€ that nothing and no one else ever again makes us feel small, worthless, or theirs.
.
.
but what if there was another truth, one that caused us to feel worthy not because we belong to no one, but because we belong to the only one worthy of our love and attention? what if we felt encouraged and empowered not because our bodies and lives are our own, but because they are married to and honored by a lord and king who calls us his most beautiful bride?
.
.
i am not my own...the day i gave my life to christ was the day i entrusted my body, my heart, my soul to the one who â€œfearfully and wonderfully madeâ€ me, and who daily gives my life meaning, purpose, and worth. what does it look like to live and breathe in that truth? what does it feel like to know my worth comes from a god who gave his life to give me mineâ€”and not from the things i do or the things that are done to me? .
.
you are loved and worthy of love, sisters. believe it.
.
.

text: r e v o l u t i o n âœŠğŸ¼ the fact this article exists makes me sad and happy at the same time. sad that something as important as  womenâ€™s health is treated with such careless disregard at a time in the 21st century when society deems it important that â€œalexaâ€ can do our entire weekly shop and have it delivered to our door by the afternoon with just the utterance of her name. absurd. however, it also makes me happy because at last (better late than never) we are opening up and talking honestly about the importance of womenâ€™s health and the monumental experience that is the journey to becoming a mother. iâ€™m not one for making conventional new yearâ€™s resolutions (not unless they are steeped in ritual, lit by a million candles at my crystal lined alter) but 2019 is the year that i am vowing to make huge change in the motherhood community. bold statement i know. but if you canâ€™t be bold, whatâ€™s the point right? donâ€™t be fooled, iâ€™m not arrogant enough to think i can do it on my own. 2019 for me is about building a strong and wise community to help me make this much needed change. iâ€™m extremely excited that on monday i will be recording my podcast interview with @drrebeccamoore, just one of the wonderful women sharing their motherhood wisdom on my upcoming podcast â€œmotherhood, redefinedâ€. the podcast is an honest journey into motherhood facilitated by wise women imparting their real life knowledge to help educate and inspire a new age in motherhood. iâ€™m so excited to share it with you in the next few months. did i mention iâ€™m excited? anyhow, in the meantime if you too are inspired to make a difference or to speak out honestly then do it. reach out to me or anyone else and make your voice heard. there will always be someone listening. ğŸ§¡ #motherhoodredefined #motherhood #newmum #pregnancy #calmmutha #revolution #newpodcast #makebirthbetter #metoomovement #metoo #feminism #motherhoodrising

text:
i was walking down a narrow street
where i met a boldly man of six feet
he wore a turban round his head
his presence made me depressed
his attitude i didn't found nice
what could i have done, i wasn't wise
he came closer, i was mum
not able to understand, where to run
his clumsy hands went down my zip
and at that small age i felt like zilch 
not able to understand what was happening
i knew it was wrong and i was trembling
he told me to be quite and said
everything's alright
i was so terrified, i just ran from the site
after reaching home i went to my room
told nothing of this to anyone and cried till noon
years passed, years passed i grew up
i grew up as a teenage
that man's face, that man's fear
never left me and my space
at school i was fine, i was fine with my friends and i was fine till nine
after that i was all alone again in my room
back to those memories and making some rules
my family never knew i wept every night
even terrified by my own father's and brother's touch
their lovely touch i felt like knifes
knifes that were cutting my soul apart
so apart it was destroyed.
.
.
.

text:
it's rare for me to be at a loss for words, but this has me very close. admittedly, i did not watch the two episodes in entirety yet...but the parts i saw made my stomach churn, skin crawl, and blood boil.  the managers and crew all are guilty of assisting this vile excuse of a man to prey on vulnerable children.  admitting to forging wedding documents, knowingly prowling for young girls at malls, etc.  you all should be ashamed of yourselves!! what if it was your daughter? 
i know his music was on top back in the 90s and early 2000s, and would never say he is without talent.  but, he should be held accountable for his actions. 
to those who spoke out and shared their stories...you may have endured unspeakable acts of abuse, but you are not broken.  continue your healing.  live your truth.  we hear you! 
#lifetime #lifetimetv #survivingrkelly #muterkelly #dreamhampton #johnlegend #roxanegay #metoo #protectourchildren #protectourdaughters

text: #31daysofsustainableliving day 17: we are getting ready to leave our 1 month vacation in australia. while here i disconnected from work, sm and the news cycle and reconnected with friends (plus dragged one from new york to join us), family and my home country. most importantly, i rediscovered hopes, dreams and desires iâ€™d long forgotten or paused while in ny. we spent more time in nature than i think i have since i moved away 10 years ago and i realized that my path was always going to lead me towards fighting for climate justice. it has filled me with immeasurable joy to see adelaide embrace and enjoy my home country as though it were her own across three states and too many stops for a two year old to gracefully endure. it is truly one of the most beautiful countries on earth - even if some of the local sayings are pure nonsense (yeah... nah). feeling grateful for all of the twists and turns, learning, and friendship that 2018 brought and everyone who supported the first year of @thefrontlash with generosity of knowledge and spirit. ready for a 2019 full of activism, sustainable fashion, and politics. until next time, australia ğŸ‡¦ğŸ‡ºğŸŒğŸ’› weâ€™ll miss you. thank you everyone who made this a special trip. itâ€™s one we wonâ€™t forget. p.s i brought so many beautiful sustainably made dresses with me but in the end i mostly wore my organic cotton t-shirt dresses from @bassike, my swimsuit from bassike and a fabulous new years dress from @maggiemarilyn . the sustainable fashion lewks will have to wait for new york summer â¤ï¸

text:
in the 90s he married a teenager and then years later allegedly he was on video having sex, giving money and golden showers to a minor... the defense argued the man in the video was not kelly, and the girl in video was not a minor... he was acquitted. â€œeight of the seated jurors were white and four were black, and that remained the jury's racial makeup after a white female juror was replaced tuesday morning by one of four alternates, a white male.â€ - thr 5/2008 "the 27-minute homemade video shows a man having sex with a young female, who is naked for most of the recording except for a necklace with a cross dangling from it.

at the start of the videotape, the man hands the female money and she mouths the words, "thank you." she is often blank-faced, impassive. the man speaks to the female in a hushed, monotone voice, and she calls him "daddy." songs from the spice girls and backstreet boys blare from a radio. the female dances -- the man out of view. back in view, he has sex with her. the man walks up to the camera to adjust it a few times, but his face is often obscured.

prosecutors say the man in the video is kelly, and that the female is a girl who was as young as 13 when the tape was made between jan. 1, 1998, and nov. 1, 2000.

the singer, who has pleaded not guilty, faces up to 15 years if convicted.

during opening statements in the long-delayed trial, cook county prosecutor shauna boliker warned jurors they would have to watch a videotape depicting an "underage child performing sex acts that you have never seen before." "a child doesn't choose to be violated and placed on a videotape, a videotape that will live on forever -- long after this child becomes an adult," boliker said.

defense attorneys, however, told jurors in their opening statements that kelly is not the man on the tape and called the video's origins into question. the defense also told jurors that the girl who authorities allege is depicted on the tape is not her at all.  #metoo #whosnext #rkelly

at the start of the videotape, the man hands the female money and she mouths the words, "thank you." she is often blank-faced, impassive. the man speaks to the female in a hushed, monotone voice, and she calls him "daddy." songs from the spice girls and backstreet boys blare from a radio. the female dances -- the man out of view. back in view, he has sex with her. the man walks up to the camera to adjust it a few times, but his face is often obscured.

prosecutors say the man in the video is kelly, and that the female is a girl who was as young as 13 when the tape was made between jan. 1, 1998, and nov. 1, 2000.

the singer, who has pleaded not guilty, faces up to 15 years if convicted.

during opening statements in the long-delayed trial, cook county prosecutor shauna boliker warned jurors they would have to watch a videotape depicting an "underage child performing sex acts that you have never seen before." "a child does not choose to be violated and placed on a videotape, a videotape that will live on forever -- long after this child becomes an adult," boliker said.

defense attorneys, however, told jurors in their opening statements that kelly is not the man on the tape and called the video's origins into question. the defense also told jurors that the girl who authorities allege is depicted on the tape is not her at all.  #metoo #whosnext #rkelly
